import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['job'] = data['job'].astype('category')
    job_counts = data['job'].value_counts().reset_index()
    job_counts.columns = ['job', 'count']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='count', y='job', data=job_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job titles in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Job Titles')
    plt.legend(title='Job Titles', loc='upper right', labels=job_counts['job'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='count', hue='sex', data=data)
    plt.title('How has the number of jobs changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Sex')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Job Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    data['percentile'] = pd.qcut(data['count'], q=10, labels=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='percentile', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count across different percentiles?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Percentile')
    plt.ylabel('Job Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
